cult, because you have to teach your people what needs to be done.  So it comes back to communication.  Note 1-4 above say &quot;yell&quot; and not &quot;ask nicely&quot;.  Yelling, or, more accurately, not being nice (kinda hard to really yell in EQ <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) tends to convey the message more efficiently, lets people understand that it's important immediately, and not &quot;oh, I'll do it whenever I remember&quot;.  All in all, it's difficult to tank with a large group of melees whether small, medium, or large race...with enough bodies, one can easily get pushed out of range...it's just a matter of getting your people to work with you, and not just madly rushing in to get some blood on their hands. <p><table width=350 height=120 border=1 style="border-color:#000000; border-width:3; border-style:solid;font-family:Arial;" cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0><tr><td background="http://www.guardianalliance.org/gfx/gasig.jpg" style="border-style:none;">   <img src="http://www.guardianalliance.org/gfx/x.gif" width=30 align=left>   <table border=0 cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 width=200>      <tr>      <td>         <font color=#FFFFFF size=+1>         <b><center>         <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45412"          style="text-decoration:none; color: #ffffff;"><u>Thak Havocblade         </a>         </u>         </b><br></font>      </td>      </tr>      <tr>      <td>         <font color=#969696 size=-1><center>Myrmidon of Brell's 59th Keg         </center>      </td>      </tr>      <tr>      <td>         <font color=#969696 size=-1><center><a href="http://www.guardianalliance.org" style="text-decoration:none; color: #969696;"><u>Guardian Alliance</u></a></center>      </td>      </tr>      <tr>      <td>         <font color=#969696 size=-1><cente