 BOLD END--> easier to move through/over/around a crowd, I find myself getting stuck between others much less frequently.  Secondly, this makes it slightly easier for others to see me.<br><br>With respect to others being able to see me, well, that should not be such a big issue, in my opinion.  At the beginning of a pull, I will be out front and visible to everyone.  When a mob is engaged and it gets a bit more crowded, in <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> most</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> cases, people do not need to see me.  They should be hitting their Assist key to get the target, and if they have PC names turned off, the targetted mob's name should be flashing and relatively easy to see.  They do not need to see me to find the mob.<br><br>There will be times when positioning relative to the MT/MA is important; however, in those cases, I would be out front and very visible.  Once melee begins, I am responsible for maintaining my position as best as aggro control by others allows and the other melees are responsible for keeping their same position relative to the mob.  Once you get in a situation like this, height of the MT/MA becomes much less important for visibility as positioning will usually keep him in the clear.<br><br><br> <p>Zigglewort the Wind Caller <BR>Halfling Warrior of 60 Seasons<BR>Sword of Fate<BR>Prexus Server<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ueqin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>eqin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/16/02 10:32:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1673.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_eyes.gif" align=absmiddle>  re:</span><hr size=1> Thanks all for